			<ns0:name>krasin@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/krasin@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
Currently, the primary PNaCl repositories are Mercurial-based. 

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;

utman.sh has to duplicate a subset of gclient functionality, which complicates the script a lot.

At the same time, gclient does not support hg and adding the support is a non-trivial effort that would complicate depot_tools a lot. I have discussed this possibility with maruel@ who is the primary developer behind depot_tools and he has discourages adding hg support.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;

Move PNaCl repositories to git (Robert Muth has suggested that it's already in our plans, but there's no bug for that. So, I have filed one)

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
No mercurial repositories are in use.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
This will uniform our code base and will make it possible to simplify utman.sh by starting to use depot_tools.

